# views/board_lab.go — SPIKE (board-lab)

Minimal Go handler for BOARD_LAB. Serves two things:

- `/gopher/board-lab/` — HTML page (nav chrome + a root
  div + elm.js bootstrap script).
- `/gopher/board-lab/elm.js` — compiled Elm bundle read
  from `games/lynrummy/board-lab/elm/elm.js`.

That's it. All puzzle-session creation and action
persistence happens via the existing `lynrummy-elm`
endpoints (new-puzzle-session, actions, etc.). No new Go
endpoints were added for the lab — the Elm app talks to
the already-working wire.

## Status

- **Label:** SPIKE (board-lab). Active-but-stable. If
  BOARD_LAB grows its own persistent state (notes, named
  puzzle catalog served as JSON), new endpoints will land
  here.

## Registered at

`views/registry.go`:

```go
mux.HandleFunc("/gopher/board-lab/", HandleBoardLab)
mux.HandleFunc("/gopher/board-lab", HandleBoardLab)
```

## Build-step

`ops/start` compiles Lab.elm to elm.js alongside the main
client's build. Rebuild is non-fatal — on failure the
handler returns a helpful 404 pointing at the check
script.

## Pointers

- Elm app: `games/lynrummy/board-lab/elm/src/Lab.elm`.
- Main app handler (reused for play + persistence):
  `views/lynrummy_elm.go`.
